---
description: Security rules for the sample todo app
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never write, log, echo, or expose secrets, API keys, `.env` values, or production credentials.
- Never use `eval` or similar dynamic execution on user input.
- Never use `html_safe` or `raw` on untrusted user input.
- Use parameterized queries and ActiveRecord query methods; never string-interpolate SQL.
- Do not disable CSRF protection, mass assignment protection, or session security checks.
- Do not read or rely on files ignored by `.cursorignore`.